<Text>I want to clarify that I am talking about Volunteers of America on Garey not the actual shelter on Mission. I'm just looking for help with my rent but if you actually need a place to stay the shelter was first come first serve. I  just started at VOA but the people were very nice, they have sack lunches, small toiletries for free.  They're going to help me with my first month's rent and deposit so I can get off the street. So far so good and most of the reviews have been really good.  They took my information  and started helping me immediately. The only thing I would advise is just to go in don't call. <username>Diana Thomsen<//username>< Date>
1616817571212< /Date>
<rate>4</rate><review>Tasty, although the chicken broth wasn't as flavorful as I prefer, and it was a tad oily. My biggest complaint, though, was with the onion. That pile of white in the middle of the bowl is finely minced onion. And with the broth not being hot enough to cook the onion, that meant I basically had a bowl full of raw onion...and that's about all I could taste. Now, in all fairness, it was cold and windy and we had to eat outside because of COVID so that's probably why the broth cooled too quickly. Still, it wasn't a good taste. However, the noodles were wonderful. Perfectly cooked and with a great texture. I would be interested in trying this again even I can eat inside to see if that fixes the temperature issue.< /review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPslQiRX8Gc7SlxDv_-YAWkW8AgQZm02xzl-RS_=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pictures><resp>None< /resp>< gmapID>

< user_id>
101558439845826242757</user_id>
<gmap_id>0x80c2c647d062b94b:0xb51b167774372606</gmap_id>< review>
Look, you *could* stand out in front of that other ramen joint down the street (owned by the same people, funny enough) for an hour like a sucker, or you can get a better bowl of ramen here. Your call.

The key difference between Hachioji and Daikokuya is the use of Shio and Shoyu broth at the former (salt and soy sauce base) and Tonkotsu (pork stock) at the later. This creates a lighter tasting ramen that might be more pleasing on your palate and easier to eat in hotter weather.

Hachioji a great combo selection, kaarage in my example, the duck in my shio ramen was delicious, and the green tea IPA deserves two rounds.

I never give cash only spots like this one a five, so read my rating as 4.5.</review>

Cash only with an ATM inside. Street parking around, but I wouldn't plan on being able to park close to the restaurant. Typically ramen offerings alongside some in-house vegan specialties that I haven't seen before (red and white ramen, a mix of miso). I ordered the Shoyu and a unique matcha beer offered and thoroughly enjoyed both. Great service on top this with an authentic, but sometimes random, ambience I've come to love at ramen stops in LA. <pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMKzol-FNsO4IUBnbtAmlU9S4duzrmgMK7Uj6b2=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPzWIPxZNGTXadsF8fcxwVcvpphBNh-IkloqYaR=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN57sIIK6yjKNah6jlGkrlhci_1iaoQHX8rSE13=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pics><response>{'time': 1584047226467, 'text': 'Thank you for your review, we greatly appreciate your visit!'}< /response><gmap_id>0x80c2c647d062b94b:0xb51b167774372606< /gmap_id><UserId.>101558439845826242757< /UserId.>< date>
1580324197535<//date>
<review>Look, you *could* stand out in front of that other ramen joint down the street (owned by the same people, funny enough) for an hour like a sucker, or you can get a better bowl of ramen here. Your call.

The key difference between Hachioji and Daikokuya is the use of Shio and Shoyu broth at the former (salt and soy sauce base) and Tonkotsu (pork stock) at the later. This creates a lighter tasting ramen that might be more pleasing on your palate and easier to eat in hotter weather.

Hachioji a great combo selection, kaarage in my example, the duck in my shio ramen was delicious, and the green tea IPA deserves two rounds.

I never give cash only spots like this one a five, so read my rating as 4.5.</review><name>mrbadguysan</name><rating>5</rating></record></dataset><record>

<review>I‚Äôm a regular of Daikokuya and I like to explore ramen places. I am very picky about the quality of my food.
This place has excellent ramen (spicy is pretty good) and excellent atmosphere.
I walked into the one next door... and had to leave... the environment felt weird, everyone was talking all low, there was no music.

<Gmap_id>0x80c2c647d062b94b:0xb51b167774372606</Gmap_id>< text>
I like Hachioji because it's close to my office but also because the prices are reasonable for the area. I love the karaage bowl ($7.50) that they have here and I usually only come here for that. I tried out the Shio ramen (with duck) once but it wasn't as good as other restaurants in Little Tokyo. The duck had a very distinct flavor to it that I've never tasted in duck though. It came with some raw onions and soft bamboo shoots.

Service is good and the salad, if you get it, is great. I think it's lettuce with corn and thousand island. The restaurant isn't crowded during lunch time.</text>

(Translated by Google) A place that at first glance you do not put much faith, I at least did not, but it was amazing and the food is very tasty, with generous portions.

A good choice is the combo, which you can choose a noodle with another dish, gives two people to eat quietly, if none is way too starving.

The ramem is very tasty, the broth is well made, leaves a good taste in the mouth, but without getting that rancid fat, so common in ramems. Takoyaki is very well made too, something that is not easy to find elsewhere, worth the request.

And the price is not exorbitant, you can eat well, without leaving your pants, but it's cash only.

English BR

A place that at first glance you do not put much faith, I at least did not, but it was amazing and the food is very tasty, with generous portions.

A good choice is the combo, which you can choose a noodle with another dish, gives two people to eat quietly, if none is strangled.

The ramem is very tasty, the broth is well made, leaves a good taste in the mouth, but without getting that rancid fat, so common in ramems. Takoyaki is very well made too, something that is not easy to find in Brazil, worth the request.

And the price is not exorbitant, you can eat well, without leaving your pants, but only accept money.

And the price is not exorbitant, you can eat well, without leaving your pants, but it's cash only.

<Gmap_id>0x80db21e58a822f75:0x996929332e787740<//Gmap_id><Name>Amie Friederich<//Name>< Text>
The majority of the people here are so very kind. Particularly those involved with food distribution.
Even with hundreds of people to deal with and even if not there consistently I am recognized. Friendly, caring smiles are a given as is patient, gentle instruction.
Though friendly, appreciation towards them is far more rare indeed.
This is the only such place I have known to take care to make sure to route necessary line in the shade areas. No small thing in temps from 90-115 degrees.
FYI; the schedule for the food bank just changed. Friday 4-6pm instead of Tuesdays.
(No doubt, seeing me and recalling apparently that I am not there as regular, a lovely woman with a beauteous smile made a point to approach me to let me know)
The Angels walking the earth are not strangers to this place.
Thank you folks and God Bless you all.
FYI</Text>

< Text>
I work for a nonprofit organization called ATAP, I was recently hired on 04/22/2019
I am a Residential Service Coordinator with ATAP..
I am to implement activities, programs and projects for our Senior Community at our local Low income Senior Apartments..
I contacted Theresa,she is the Church‚Äôs Free Food Coordinator, about what my vision and ideas were ..
I felt a need for the Low income Seniors to receive Free Food..
Many of our Local Seniors who live in these Senior Apartments are unable to get around.. Then their are Seniors known as  ‚Äú Shut Inns‚Äù
Most if not all live On SSI, Disability, Social Security,and have no other means of money..
I have spoken with many Seniors at our apartments, when they pay their monthly rent, utilities several of our seniors only have a few dollars left..
Seriously some only have the sum of, $ 100 all the way to $10 left to buy Food for themselves ALL MONTH LONG..!!
So, I have Spoken with Theresa our seniors ‚ÄòFood Angel ‚Äú üòáüëºüèº
She and St. Elizabeth Church In Desert Hot Springs, Ca have partnered up with ATAP  Senior Program to come to THEM ..
Theresa and a few Volunteers come over to our Low Income Senior Apartments, Every Other Saturday morning for 1/2 am hour to hand out much needed supplemental food to our local Senior Residents of Desert Hot Springs..!!
I thank God that I was able to implement such a wonderful project..
I have a job to do , I will get it done ..!
My Job is to help the ones who need it, and make it happen, I have many more programs and projects I will Be implementing through out our local community..

If there is a will , There is a way..!!
God Bless You Theresa and all the Volunteers, and for the Church..
Your Food Distribution Services On
05/18/2019 and continued support will always be honored on behalf of Myself and ATAP ..!!
Thank You üôèüèª..!!!<//Text>

Checked this place out for happy hour.  Pretty average.

Sushi is not bad.  Lots of shrimp tempura options, which I like.  Happy hour prices seem on par with local competition such as Kabuki.  The hot sake seemed watered down or maybe just cheaper that other places I have ordered it from.  Service is slow and took a while to just get plain sushi.

<userid>101276026063135721806</userid><Name>Trisha Williams</Name><Review>Price is  good< /Review><Date>1567720549864</Date><Rate>4</Rate><gmapID>0x80c2c37229b064a9:0xdb0b3d8fd2481871< /gmapID></record>
</dataset><record>
< Rate>

< GmapID>
0x80c2c37229b064a9:0xdb0b3d8fd2481871</GmapID>
< userid>
100934048083327874295</userid>
< Review>
It's kinda funny that what I enjoyed the most here was the seaweed salad and the tempura ice cream.

I ordered the Cute Devil after asking for a recommendation from the server.  Their menu has a lot of variety, so it's great in that aspect.  However, the Cute Devil was not so great.  It was very rich.  The description does say that it's shrimp tempura and spicy crab salad inside, and raw fish and more spicy crab salad on top.  Too much creaminess from crab salad, bleh.  What caught my eye in the picture was the raw fish, but the slices of fish were rather thin (disappointing because I was looking for that freshness), and the tempura was SUPER crispy... like way too crispy... like "where's the shrimp at?" too crispy because all I can taste is crispy tempura batter.

For that reason, my friend and I were debating whether or not to get the tempura ice cream, expecting it to be super extra too crispy like the shrimp tempura.  But fortunately, the tempura green tea ice cream was delicious.  The dough was lightly crispy on the outside and slightly chewy overall.  The ice cream was creamy... it was a good way to end the meal.

Hm, I don't know if it was mentioned on the menu or anywhere in the restaurant, but they give you a discount if you pay with cash instead of credit card.  Had I known that before, we wouldn't have ordered like fatties.  We were short on cash by a couple bucks (and therefore too short too tip also), so we ended up paying with credit card.

The prices are reasonable and the service is good.  This is not the place if you are looking for authentic Japanese sushi, but otherwise it's ok!

Street parking< /Review>
< Date>
1415953262373<//Date>
< name>
Muy S< /name>

<pictures>None< /pictures><username>Cheryl Myrick< /username><response>None< /response><Review>I'm a displaced victim of the CA Camp Fire where my car was damaged beyond repair.  After waiting over 3wks for a rental to become available I was forced to drive w/my special needs child and his service dog, in a totaled and dangerous car almost 100 mi to get the ONLY car available.

Unable to travel at more than 40 mph due to the condition of my car, I knew I would arrive a few mins after closing. When I called the office to explain the issue I was met by a counter agent w/open hostility. She felt compelled to remind of their business hours and informed me that the computers would automatically shut down at 5pm. She then stated 'there is nothing I can do for you!

After letting her know I was aware of the business hours, I told her I was hoping an exception might be made to prevent my son and I spending the night in their parking lot that my car would NOT make the return trip. I was sure there was someone there with authority to keep the computers on for a few minutes longer. After sitting on hold for a ridiculously long time, she returned stating in a nasty tone, "we'll give you FIVE minutes!" ms she hung up!

After this encounter I called a friend I hadn't spoken with in yrs hoping he still worked 20mins away from the agency. He offered to immediately leave his job to go there and wait for me. Unfortunately I got lost. I was 8 mins late instead of 5 as I'd hoped. Just as I was pulling into the parking lot I witnessed my friend, who'd been directing me over the phone as to how to find them, being pushed by a clerk who was attempting to lock me out!

When I got to the counter I was greeted by the same unpleasant clerk I dealt with on the phone. Still hostile, she asked when I intended to return the vehicle.  Having no idea how long it might take to replace my burned car, I was unable to provide an exact date but agreed to call to request an extension by a specified date. A call I made to a LOCAL branch two days before that deadline. I was relieved to have reached a very pleasant counter agent who informed me their computers had gone down therefore she would have to take my info by hand and enter it when they came back up. Only later, when returning the vehicle, did I learn that did not occur.

Two weeks prior to returning the vehicle, unable to reach anyone via the 'contact us' link online at Budget's corporate office, I was forced to settle for writing a letter of grievance to the co's customer service dept in hopes the individuals involved might be held accountable for such vile treatment of a customer. For my trouble I received a computer generated form letter the next day apologizing for the inconvenience? A form letter!

In spite of giving them two days prior notice, the rental car was dirty at pick up, I had to have it jump started by strangers on three separate occasions, and I still returned spotless and full!

Because the local agent could find no record of my request for an extension he refused to provide me with a receipt! He stated I'd have to take the matter up with the 'office of origin'. At that I requested to speak to a manager. I waited over an hour while he called around trying to find one. Whoever he spoke with promised to immediately call back while I was still there. The call never came but I did finally get a receipt.

Frustrated and made late picking up my son, only later did I notice I'd been charged a $400 late fee!? A letter protesting these outrageous charges was met with another email restating policy & a 'gift' of $100 refund! After all I'd endured this is an insult! It's outright thievery! It's now a matter of principle having little to do with $ and everything to do w finding justice!

Why is no one held accountable for abusive treatment of customers? Why are consumers held responsible for the poor training of employees who provide inaccurate or inadequate info? Why are customers painted w/the same broad brush, seen as potential crooks on the take & treated accordingly? We can't stop this practice with silence!

Budget Rent A Car customers BEWARE!
Find another option!</Review>< Time>

<Review>I went to this Subway #136 at 1770 S. Harbor to order a breakfast sandwich.  The store is smaller than most subways and kind of dirty.

The girl who made the sandwich had a hard time with English.  That is OK. However, she acted like as if she was doing me a big favor making the sandwich.  I specifically asked her twice for regular egg, not egg whites, and she still put an egg white paddy in the sandwich and popped it in the oven.

I asked her again if it was or was not egg whites.  Finally, when she realized that she had made a mistake, she took the egg white paddy out of the oven and to my surprise put it back in the fridge to serve it to the next customer after seeking the manager's approval!

She then put a regular egg paddy in the same bread and put it back in the oven again.  I was sick to my stomach after eating the sandwich.

I also noticed that the other workers there, including the manager, kept going in the back and moving things around and when they came to the counter to serve the customers they never changed their gloves and handled the food,  the money, the register and the trash with all the same gloves.

They apparently have no clue that  they are supposed to use the gloves to prevent the food from getting contaminated and that they should change the gloves after handling trash, etc.

Disgusting place, rude employees and bad attitudes.  I would give this place zero stars if I could.  It also seems like the menu was more expensive than other locations and  they offered no specials.<//Review>< user_name>

<Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
My 2020 Mazda had a slow tire leak, and the dealership discovered a long, thin nail near the sidewall; the tire had to be replaced. Yet they didn't have the tire in stock and couldn't guarantee they could get it in by the next morning! A planned trip to Palm Springs was in jeopardy...
So, Pacific Coast Tire to the rescue! I called from the dealership, and Mike was more than helpful. Yes, he could get the tire and yes, if I came in first thing in the morning, he'd get me back on the road in 60-90 minutes. Mike delivered on all of his promises, and I was one happy customer on the way to the desert. As an added bonus, the total cost with an alignment was $160 less than what the dealership quoted! With such a great experience, I know I can rely on Pacific Coast Tire in the future. But hopefully not too soon!</Review>

< Review>
Everyone knows that this Tire Center could run around the clock.  I agree!  Astonishing friendly, intelligent (and patient with the novices) service - members have their flat tires fixed free; for a tire not purchased there it is $14-$28.

AND they have a free, sophisticated air hose right outside the center for use at any time.  A cordial serviceman came out and helped me with it. AND when I needed a a replacement tire on a new car, the service manager candidly told me how to save money by just buying one tire instead of the COSTCO required two since my other tires were in sound shape. Appointments are also now available!  It used to be first-come, first serve.<//Review>

< text>
I've had several appointments here, and all have been very good to excellent. Never has anyone upsold me, over-promised or be anything other than polite and professional. Making appointments helps a ton, but I've dropped in for torque or inflation checks with no problem.
I've gone in for four tires and they've shown me I could do with only two, but left the choice up to me.
Although, I wouldn't count on it, they've slipped me in when there was a slow spot for a tire repair.
Joe took care of me last time and I'd recommend him for service.<//text>

You have to call multiple times just to get through. When you finally get through, they may put you on hold.  Then, after keeping you on hold for a while, they may hang up on you, forcing you to start the whole process again.

This is not to mention that they don't even do a good job.  I was told I could keep driving on two of my tires for at least 5,000 more miles.  I got an oil change after another 1,000-2,000 miles and was told the tires were horrible and needed to be replaced immediately.  When I went to Costco and asked them to check those two tires again, the guy looked at ONE of the two tires and said I was fine for a little while longer.  I had to ask him to check the second tire.  Upon checking the second tire, he said, "oh yeah, this one needs to get replaced soon."  So irresponsible.  Costco shouldn't allow this quality of service.

Also, for the two new tires that I did buy, the tires were already almost one year old.  I'm not sure if this is normal, but I'd prefer my new tires to have as little shelf life as possible.< /Text>

Pizza by the slice...nothing more, nothing less. Pretty decent and affordable place in the neighborhood to grab a slice after a boozy night. For $5 slice, you can get variety of options which include vegetarian ones like veggie, cheese and pesto. One slice is pretty filling for one person. You're lucky if you get a fresh hot slice just out of the oven. There's a very small seating area too, and colas / water to buy.< /review>

<text>THE GOOD:

Honestly, can't think of one

THE NOT SO GOOD:

Cold pizza
not cooked enough
Vegetarian pizza is a joke

I hardly ever give a 1 star rating but this place disappointed us on so many levels. We had both ordered 2 wholes pizzas, My pizza was barely warm when I got to eat it, We were less than 5 minutes away from the pizza shop, So distance is not an issue regarding that matter.

On top of that, the dough had clearly not been cooked enough as it was still slightly uncooked in the middle.

The other pizza that we ordered was a Vegetarian pizza, which consisted of a few olives, mushrooms, peppers and tomatoes. One of the worse vegetarian pizzas I had ever seen and because there were no descriptions of the pizzas, one had no idea what they were getting. The pizza was also not hot and cooked through.

On a side note, something that I observed whilst there, someone had not received their whole order, they then had to make the pizza after they had received their first pizza which by the time they had gotten their second pizza, the first had been standing for over 10 minutes. I honestly do not know how places like this stay in business, my feeling is because there are so many hotels around that people only really eat here once.< /text><Pics>None</Pics><Resp>None<//Resp>< GmapID>

<user_name>Mark Farrar< /user_name><date>1600187971189< /date><gmap_id>0x80c299b1e5ec1335:0x3c75b1556c8eb77c<//gmap_id>< Rate>

<resp>{'time': 1600607835664, 'text': 'Thank you very much for such a great review, Mark! We‚Äôre really glad you liked our service. Please let us know if there‚Äôs anything we can ever do for you.\n\n- Sam Mollaei Esq.'}<//resp>< Review>
Earlier this year, I needed an ITIN and while I know I could have done this entirely by myself, I would rather pay somebody who knows the system to do the bulk of the work for me than struggle through government websites and forms myself.

After doing a bit of research, I came across EIN Express and they seemed to offer the service I needed, at a price I was willing to pay.

For the most part, I worked with Sina Bonabi, who guided me through the process from start to finish, both via Skype calls and email.

It was an easy process, with no hiccoughs, and although it took longer than usual to be issued with my ITIN, this was entirely because of delays caused by the coronavirus scare (e.g. staffing shortages in the relevant government department), and not because of any problems with Sina and his company.

So, if you‚Äôre looking for somebody to work with you to obtain a tax identification number, I would highly recommend using their ITIN Service. (They offer other services too, such as the formation of an LLC or Corporation, obtaining an EIN, and opening US bank accounts, but I haven‚Äôt used those so cannot comment on them yet.)< /Review>

< review>
I came across Sina Bonabi and the EIN Express service via google search. After a lot of research I got in touch and was very very impressed by the level of customer service and attention I received. It was an easy decision after that. I am a foreigner living outside the US and needed my ITIN for corporate use. Honestly I was stressed and overwhelmed about the processing being that I have not had previous dealings with the IRS. Sina and the team were friendly, encouraging and uber professional. The wait time understandably was far longer than expected, due to COVID of course but Sina gave me regular updates, always responded within 24 hours and honestly the process was so smooth and uncomplicated thanks to their team. I will be in need of a EIN in the future and there is no doubt I will be using Sina and EIN Express team for this as well. Highly highly recommend this service for anyone who needs support with applying for an ITIN or EIN.</review>

<Review>In tough times you need people to step up to the plate.  Covid is and has not been an easy road not only on personal levels but business as well.  I placed a request to get an ITIN number back in November 2020. Went through the whole process of supplying all the requirements they need to process my request and then things at the US Government started to slow down.  In constant communication with Sina's team, they kept advising me that they were processing requests for specific months at a time.  I finally got my ITIN at the end of January 2021.  During all this time Sina personally responded back and kept me in the loop and was super professional about it - as was I.  It does not pay to bark - you get way more done with Honey - I was tought.  We both appreciated and knew that we were in a waiting game. <Time>1597204062450< /Time><Rating>5</Rating><Review>I was looking to start a company and reached out on FB to friends/fam for a lawyer reference. Shortly after I saw an add for Mollaei Law. I checked out their site and their reviews. The site honestly put me off a bit at first, but their reviews were on point so I decided to give it a try.

The scheduling aspect was very easy, I got an email clearly outlining the expectations from me as well as a calendar invite. It's novel but I like that they went so far to make sure you clearly understood the expectations and had a set date/time to meet. This first appointment was a short block designed to assess my needs, it was free and the gentleman I spoke to was very professional and knowledgeable. He was able to answer all of my questions and I felt confident about proceeding.

The price honestly was a little on the steeper end but I do feel I got my value out of it and going in I had no idea what this sort of service should cost so I made no effort to haggle. The price was affordable and reasonable for this type of service. All registration fee's and everything was included in the one quoted price so it was really nice not to have any sort of hidden or last minute "fees".

The registration only took about a week which was great, they sent over all the documentation for everything when they were done (so I didn't have to wait for a package in the mail or anything). I was able to confirm on the state secretary website for my state and I saw my business there, everything looks to be in standing order.

Post registration they have continued to support me as well via email chains which is great since as a new business owner I have a lot of questions!

Overall I had a great experience and would definitely recommend using them and can see hiring them for additional services in the future.< /Review>< Pics>
None< /Pics>

<user>104295473294632204189<//user>< review>
I've been planning to get an ITIN number for a few years now; yet, I've always hesitated when I was required to sign tax forms and send my passport to the IRS office in the US considering it'd remain there for a couple of months. Then later I wouldn't have any chance to communicate with anyone for assistance or inquire about the status of the process.

Sina Bonabi through their ITIN Service gave me full confidence to start the process with their professional team. Since the moment the order went through, the service was great, they gave me phone calls inquiring for more personal information, set up an appointment for ID validation, informed updates through emails and I was NOT required to send my passport anywhere which was a BIG plus. Later, they were kind enough to send me photos of the IRS letter once I was assigned an ITIN number.

I'd definitely recommend their EIN Express and ITIN Service to anyone that is considering getting an ITIN number. Special thanks again to Sina Bonabi, Bridget Lopez and Mo Hajr for their support and assistance.</review>

I attempted to get ITIN through two IRS agents and all they were interested was the filling fee. They charged me and abandoned my process when IRS denied issuance of ITIN due to the fact that I did not send my International Passport by mail. Although the agents told me that the photocopy was sufficient but IRS requested for the Original copy, I was not very comfortable sending Original Document, hence I came across EIN Express, Sina Bonabi, and ITIN Service, I contacted Sina Bonabi and my case was taken app, he was very friendly and his staff too were very professional and ready to assist. <Review>Summary: As a US citizen, the services provided are not worth the amount paid. If you are starting a business and want an expensive checklist then this is for you.

I wanted to start a small business, but had no idea where to start. I came across Sam's website and it seemed as though he did everything required to help get set up. I asked a few additional questions about his services and although his responses were vague, I thought, "I'm willing to sacrifice this money to avoid making any mistakes."

I paid Sam, and he filed for my LLC that night. The next day I received an email with the certificate, and a couple of documents. The documents looked like they were more or less a template that could be copy/pasted. But it would have taken me a long time (if I even found out what papers I needed) and I was grateful.

He also sent me a checklist of other items I needed to do for compliance in my state. I tried to complete this and didn't know some of the answers to the questions. But each time I asked Sam about my state's requirements he told me he didn't deal with those specific concerns but that if I followed the steps he provided, I would be okay. Then he asked if I would leave a review.

After a few times of asking questions that were not directly answered and being asked to leave a review each time, I explained that I felt like I paid a lot of money and hadn't received much help. He replied that he did everything he promised. Considering the package is called "Start a business", what he promised was somewhat misleading. He listed out that he filed for the company, and drafted the Articles of Organization, etc. I did not know what else it took to start a business, and the site leaves out the fact that there is actually a lot more to do after you "start a business". So I told him, yes, you did everything you told me you would do, however, I explained that his site was vague in certain areas, and I would post an honest review so people are aware of what they are getting into.

He responded with an email saying "Why are you giving me a hard time at this point?" This didn't seem very professional, I was not being rude or threatening, just telling him what some of my pain points were so he could have a chance to address them. I told him I was just trying to get his side before posting my review, and reminded him he had stated that "My service also comes with a 100% Money-Back Guarantee: if you're not satisfied with my service for any reason, just let me know within 30 days and I will issue you a full refund of the service fee." (Direct from the website and email), and told him that I was not satisfied and would like my money back. He did not respond.

Four days later, I emailed and told him I was leaving a review, and he responded within thirty minutes. He told me that his money back guarantee is typically for clients who he hasn‚Äôt completely rendered the service for. But from now on, in order not to upset anyone like me, he will remove the Money Back Guarantee.

In conclusion, it seems he deals primarily with people that are foreign to the US. Maybe his services for them are great. Personally If I am paying as much as I did, I would expect my business to be operational and to be able to sell when 'service is fully rendered' by a company that sells a package titled 'start a business'.< /Review>< Time>

He answered all my questions, usually on the same day asked, and helped me with any forms that needed filling out. Sam was great, and I would recommend his services to anyone.

I successfully used the ITIN Service of EIN Express to obtain an ITIN number.  For a couple of years before, I had failed to do so using other firms engaged in similar services. Then, I found Sina Bonabi of EIN Express on the internet, and he a quickly developed a very clear plan, that immediately seemed feasible. For a very reasonable fee, he and his associates basically completed all the necessary forms, with my involvement mostly involving general verification. Nevertheless, I still felt in complete control as Mr. Bonabi explained - in detail - every step of the process, providing me with clear options where appropriate. It is important to note that the entire process happened with me residing in Europe, and communication exclusively via email and video conferencing. I would highly recommend EIN Express to anyone needing an ITIN number.</Review>

<text>If you want to self publish and need an ITIN you need to read this. It could take a while for the ITIN but believe me its worth it.
I contacted EIN EXPRESS when i needed an ITIN in order to self publish with Amazon.
I know when people look at the price and think is it worth it? I can say it really is.
I got a response very fast from a gentleman called Sina Bonabi who asked me all about why i needed an ITIN and how the procedure works.
He emailed me some forms to fill out and mail them to his address where he would send them off to the IRS. Everything seemed to be going well until the letter came through the door saying that the IRS have rejected the application. I emailed Sina straight away and he responded that he had the news as well.
The IRS rejected my application because of the ITIN cover letter from Amazon. All Amazon do if you ask for a written cover letter is send you a self generated one which will get rejected.
So Sina got busy trying to contact Amazon and speak to one of their main guys who no one can get hold of and he also tried getting the IRS to overturn the decision. I tried asking multiple self publishing companies to write me the cover letter i needed but they all refused or said they have a different way. After a while i contacted Sina who was sky high with work and trying to balance his life trying to fix all the applications that had been rejected. He told me we can go round a different route that doesn't need a cover letter. It was brilliant and we got the ball rolling again and filled out some other forms.
After waiting patiently for so long and myself keep emailing and bothering Sina, the ITIN finally arrived and Sina contacted me over Skype to show me it's all done. Sina Bonabi has been absolutely brilliant over the last year with responding to my emails and helping me get my ITIN. Would also like to thank Sam Mollaei at EIN EXPRESS as well, plus their assistants for all their hard work.
Its very hard to get an ITIN on your own because of the cover letter situation now and the IRS. Most likely if you fill it out and send it off on your own it will get rejected. So having these two guys Sina Bonabi and Sam Mollaei at EIN EXPRESS they make the process so much easier as they are qualified and really know their legal stuff.<//text><Pictures>None< /Pictures></record></dataset><record>

I start by saying a big thank you to Sina Bonabi. Thanks to you brother, I FINALLY got my ITIN number.

I needed an ITIN number for my internet activities and for months I tried to get one on my own ... without success. I sent mails by DHL, by post and never the IRS seemed to receive them. Certainly a problem with the right address or the right department.

Then, after a few hours of research on the internet, I found many providers on the internet. I had doubts at first because I did not know if it was possible on the internet. Some providers were cheaper than EIN Express. However, EIN Express seemed more professional, so I tried it.

After the first step, I immediately received a message from Sina Bonabi who invited me to make an appointment on Skype. During the appointment everything went well. He was patient, caring and made efforts to understand my approximate English :-). Sina accompanied me throughout the process, he helped me find the right documents for me.

Once the process was completed, I received my number after only 5 weeks.

I have already recommended the service around me. Thanks again to EIN Express for this professional and fast service.

Thierry</text>

This is a scam!! Look up "Registered Agent in your State" and you will see plenty of companies that are 1/3 the price of what these people are offering. Don't fall for it, I almost did before doing research. This guy is using his lawyer credentials to make you think that you need a lawyer to start a business. You don't need a lawyer!! If you look at the responsibilities of a registered agent they will exactly match with the services that this company offers. Again, SCAMM!!!! Stay away.<//text>

< Text>
This is a scam!! Look up "Registered Agent in your State" and you will see plenty of companies that are 1/3 the price of what these people are offering. Don't fall for it, I almost did before doing research. This guy is using his lawyer credentials to make you think that you need a lawyer to start a business. You don't need a lawyer!! If you look at the responsibilities of a registered agent they will exactly match with the services that this company offers. Again, SCAMM!!!! Stay away.<//Text>

Sam helped me set up an LLC for an art business when I came to him with only half a notion about how to go about that. He was very open and helpful, answering all my questions and walking me through the process. He responded to every email the same day I sent it, and was proactive in letting me know when paperwork was filed, when it was accepted, and what to do after that.

I couldn't be happier with the help I received. Although it is technically possible to set up an LLC yourself I was not at all comfortable doing that, knowing almost nothing about the process and finding information online confusing, not knowing what to trust. Hiring Sam to guide me through that process and make sure it was done correctly and completely was well worth the cost.

If you are thinking of forming a small business entity, even if it is for some weird creative niche, I highly recommend talking to Sam. He could not have been more professional or more helpful.<//Text>

Mine was a somewhat difficult case for various reasons. I had unsuccessfully tried to apply for an ITIN on my own three times. Unlike other countries I have worked with in East Asia and Europe, the IRS have absolutely no-one on staff to deal with and/or help with questions related to the application.

Luckily I found EIN Express and Sina and they came through for me. It was not a one-week-and-it's-done fast process but neither was it slow... - as mentioned above, my situation was tricky. Sina talked to his contacts, helped me through the process and with processing my application to the IRS. I now have my ITIN. And I sincerely believe without a question of a doubt that I got it faster from EIN Express than I would have from any other similar provider of said service.

Thank you, Sina, for all your help and for getting me my ITIN when I honestly thought all hope was lost!</review>

< text>
Mine was a somewhat difficult case for various reasons. I had unsuccessfully tried to apply for an ITIN on my own three times. Unlike other countries I have worked with in East Asia and Europe, the IRS have absolutely no-one on staff to deal with and/or help with questions related to the application.

Luckily I found EIN Express and Sina and they came through for me. It was not a one-week-and-it's-done fast process but neither was it slow... - as mentioned above, my situation was tricky. Sina talked to his contacts, helped me through the process and with processing my application to the IRS. I now have my ITIN. And I sincerely believe without a question of a doubt that I got it faster from EIN Express than I would have from any other similar provider of said service.

Thank you, Sina, for all your help and for getting me my ITIN when I honestly thought all hope was lost!</text>
